\b Performance and Server Requirements Report\b0\par
Project: AI_PPT_GENERATOR\par
Date: 2026-04-06\par
\par
\b 1. Executive Summary\b0\par
This project generates presentations by calling external APIs (OpenAI LLM, Pexels/Unsplash) and then builds PPTX files locally using python-pptx. As implemented, GPU is not used by the application code. Most latency is dominated by remote API response time and network latency. Local CPU work is limited to JSON processing, image download/decoding, and PPTX assembly.\par
\par
\b 2. What Runs on CPU vs GPU\b0\par
- CPU (local): FastAPI request handling, JSON parsing, image download/decoding, PPTX generation, database IO.\par
- GPU (local): Not used by code. If the LLM is external (OpenAI), inference happens remotely.\par
- External services: OpenAI LLM API, Pexels/Unsplash image search APIs.\par
\par
\b 3. Local End-to-End Benchmark Results (LLM + Image Search + PPTX Export)\b0\par
Environment: local sandbox with outbound network; OpenAI/Pexels/Unsplash keys configured.\par
Trials: 2 per slide count. Prompt: "quarterly performance" (fixed).\par
Export step includes image downloads from returned URLs.\par
\par
Slides | LLM med s | Img med s | Export med s | Total med s | Total s/slide\par
     4 |     1.584 |     1.210 |        1.972 |       4.767 |          1.192\par
     6 |     2.137 |     1.162 |        1.401 |       4.700 |          0.783\par
     8 |     2.250 |     1.113 |        2.629 |       5.991 |          0.749\par
\par
\b Notes on Variance\b0\par
LLM and image APIs are network-bound, so timings vary by provider latency and network conditions. Export time varies with image sizes and download speed.\par
\par
