\par
\b 5. Server Requirements (Current Implementation)\b0\par
\b Software\b0\par
- Backend: Python 3.10+ with FastAPI, httpx, python-pptx.\par
- Frontend: Node.js 18+ (Vite/Vue).\par
- Database: SQLite by default (DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./ppt_generator.db).\par
- External API keys: OPENAI_API_KEY, PEXELS_API_KEY, UNSPLASH_ACCESS_KEY.\par
- Outbound HTTPS access required.\par
\par
\b Hardware (Guidance)\b0\par
Because LLM and image generation are external, local CPU/RAM requirements are modest. Actual sizing depends on concurrent users and export volume.\par
- vCPU: 2-4 for low traffic (scale with concurrency)\par
- RAM: 4-8 GB for low traffic\par
- Disk: depends on number of presentations and cached media\par
- Network: reliable outbound HTTPS with low latency\par
\par
\b 6. CPU-Only Processing Details\b0\par
- CPU handles request routing, JSON serialization, image download and decoding, and PPTX packaging.\par
- CPU load increases with concurrency and number of images per slide.\par
- GPU is not required unless you add local inference.\par
\par
\b 7. Observability Checklist\b0\par
- Log LLM request latency (OpenAI)\par
- Log image search latency (Pexels/Unsplash)\par
- Log PPTX export time\par
- Monitor CPU, memory, and response codes\par
\par
\b 8. Notes\b0\par
This report reflects the current codebase where generation uses remote APIs. If you move inference on-prem or add GPU-accelerated steps, update this report with new benchmarks.\par
